reviews/1/text:
Nhìn hấp dẫn chưa kìa trời ơi là trờiiiii

Món này và quán này, tôi mới ghé có 2 lần thôi đó các bác ơi. Mà lần nào ghé cũng phải ngồi cả tiếng, vừa ăn vừa ngắm đường vừa 888 cho no cho mệt r mới chịu về á. Tần suất ghé k cao vì đường qua đây hơi to hơi xa với tui. Chứ thật ra quán bán ngon á trời 😝😝
(Giờ lục lại loạt ảnh viết review 1 lần mà bị thèm í huhu 😞)

1 tô như vầy quên bao tiền r mn ơi (hụ hụ k bao giờ nhớ giá nổi). Nhưng topping thì như ảnh á, ứ hự luôn (tô này to chắc cỡ tô bún bò huế đặc biệt hoặc tô phở đặc biệt full topping mn hay ăn thôi nè, bình thường mình toàn ăn size đặc biệt).

Thôi nhìn ảnh là thấy thèm, mn cũng thấy nên ghé r đúng k 😭😭
(Trời ơi sao tui review tui toàn khen k ta, cái này chỉ trách tui chọn kỹ quá, sao mà toàn chọn quán nào chỗ nào hợp gu, chất lượng. Tại vì như v á nên lúc viết review toàn thấy khen k (ít chê chứ k phải k có, nhưng chỗ này là KHEN, khen thiệt lòng mn nha 🥳))
reviews/1/textTranslated:
Oh my god, it looks so delicious

I've only been to this dish and this restaurant twice. Every time I come, I have to sit for an hour, eat, watch the road, and call 888 until I'm full and tired before I leave. I don't visit often because the road here is a bit big and far for me. But actually, the restaurant is delicious 😝😝
(Now I'm looking back at the series of photos to write a review and I'm craving huhu 😞)

I forgot how much a bowl like this costs (cough, I can never remember the price). But the toppings are like the picture, oh my (this bowl is probably as big as the special Hue beef noodle bowl or the special pho bowl with full toppings that everyone eats, normally I only eat the special size).

Just looking at the picture makes me crave it, everyone should go there too, right 😭😭
(Oh my god, why do I only praise everything in my reviews? This is just because I'm too picky, why do I always choose places that suit my taste and have good quality. Because of that, when I write reviews, I only see praise (there are few criticisms, not that there are none, but this place is a PRAISE, a sincere praise everyone 🥳))

reviews/2/textTranslated: Too bad the crab soup is sold spoiled and not used for business. Who will buy it?

reviews/1/text:
-Mình ăn khá nhiều lần ở quán này, bánh quấn, chả, hành phi,... ăn được.
-Tuy nhiên chất lượng phục vụ rất tệ, đồ lên lâu, bàn thiếu nước mắm, lên nhầm món cho khách. Thái độ không thiện cảm.
-Nói chung chấp nhận được với cái giá 20k-25k ở quận 1.
-Hình ảnh: Đĩa bánh quấn 25 000 VND
reviews/1/textTranslated:
-I have eaten at this restaurant many times, the rice rolls, sausage, fried onions,... are edible.

-However, the service quality is very bad, the food takes a long time to come out, the table lacks fish sauce, the wrong dishes are served to customers. The attitude is not friendly.
-Overall, it is acceptable for the price of 20k-25k in District 1.
-Image: A plate of rice rolls 25,000 VND
reviews/2/text: Best of the best !

reviews/0/text: Thời gian mở cửa cửa hàng thì sai. Để 7h mà 6h30 đóng cửa rồi. Nhân viên thái độ rất cà chớn, ăn nói cộc lốc khó chịu.
reviews/0/textTranslated: The store opening time is wrong. It says 7pm but it closes at 6:30pm. The staff is very rude and speaks rudely.
reviews/1/text: Thái độ phục vụ thật sự tệ luôn á. Mình đến quán không có ai và bạn nhân viên đang bấm đt. Mình có chở con nhỏ theo nên đứng ngoài, bạn thấy mình nhưng nhất định không đi ra. Mình đợi phải tầm 2-3p rồi chủ động kêu mới ra nha trời ơi. Xong ra thì hỏi mình ăn gì, mình hỏi có gì thì kêu "Gì cũng có", mình bảo vậy thôi cho mình xem menu đi thì với thái đều bỉu môi bực bội không hài lòng á. Tệ thật sự
reviews/1/textTranslated: The service attitude is really bad. When I arrived at the restaurant, there was no one and the staff was on their phone. I had a small child with me so I stood outside. The staff saw me but refused to come out. I had to wait for about 2-3 minutes before they proactively called me out. When they came out, they asked me what I wanted to eat. When I asked what I wanted, they said, "We have everything." I said, "That's it, let me see the menu." They both pouted, annoyed and dissatisfied. It was really bad.
reviews/2/responseFromOwnerText:
Dạ Kyo cảm ơn phản hồi & rất xin lỗi vì trải nghiệm chưa tốt của chị ạ. 

Kyo sẽ nhắc nhở các bạn nhân viên điều chỉnh lại thái độ của mình ạ 🥰
reviews/2/text: Bạn bán hàng CN quận 4 (bạn to con) ko hiểu sao mình mua mà thái độ hằn học khó chịu với khách dữ vậy, liếc bằng nửa con mắt. Bán hàng thì ko đưa bill, mình xin lại bill thì lại tỏ vẻ khó chịu.
reviews/2/textTranslated: The salesman at District 4 branch (big guy) didn't understand why I bought it but he had such a nasty attitude towards the customer, glancing at me with half an eye. The salesman didn't give me the bill, when I asked for the bill back he acted annoyed.

reviews/1/textTranslated: 70k for a bowl of porridge without fried dough sticks, in my opinion it's a bit high, given the district 1 area. The style is a mix of Chinese and Vietnamese, calling it purely a Chinese dish is not right, the taste doesn't create a very impressive sense of cultural difference. The mixed bowl has mushrooms, squid, shrimp, pork balls... no fish, in general the toppings are not very special compared to the price. The porridge is thin, the taste is too bland for my taste. The fried dough sticks are dry and bad. There's a lot of ginger, so if you eat it on a cold rainy day, it will probably feel warmer in the stomach.

title: Cơm Bình Dân Cô Vân
address: 127a Võ Văn Kiệt, Phường Cầu Ông Lãnh, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/text: Các món ăn đều ngon, đúng khẩu vị miền Nam. Đáng để ghé thưởng thức!
reviews/0/textTranslated: The dishes are all delicious, with authentic Southern flavors. Worth a visit!
reviews/2/text:
Even though it is just a small eatery that utilises the sidewalk of Vo Van Kiet Street for customer seating, this place really surprised me.

More than 20 dishes are displayed in rows on stainless steel tables, neatly arranged and looking delicious, just like a buffet. Since it was Saturday when I visited, the owner mentioned they offer an even wider selection of dishes on weekdays.

This eatery caters to blue-collar workers, hence the incredibly affordable price of only VND 35.000 for a plate of rice. Yet, diners also receive soup, fresh vegetables, and a glass of ice for their complimentary tea already placed on the table.

100 points for the quality of food and 1000 points for the owner's attentiveness. Noticing us struggling to separate the chicken thigh meat, the owner swiftly brought scissors to our table and offered to help cut it. Her attentiveness extended to even the smallest details, observing and inquiring immediately if we show any signs of needing something.

title: VIVA FOODS
address: 29 Le Duan St Saigon Tower, Floor 16, P. Phú Thuận, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Ms. K,

Thank you for taking the time to leave a review. We appreciate your feedback and are sorry to hear that your experience with Viva Foods did not meet your expectations.

We understand your frustration with our minimum order size. At Viva Foods, we specialize in catering for larger groups, and our minimum order is currently set at 15 people. This allows us to efficiently manage our resources and provide the best possible service to our clients.

We apologize if the initial questioning about your event seemed excessive. We strive to understand our clients' needs thoroughly to offer the most suitable menu options. In your case, we were trying to determine if your gathering might be better suited for a customized order rather than our standard catering packages, which are designed for larger groups.

Regarding the menu pricing, we typically base our quotes on the number of guests to ensure we provide ample food for everyone. However, we are happy to discuss individual items and customize orders to fit specific needs and budgets. We apologize if this was not communicated clearly during our conversation.

We value all our customers and aim to provide excellent service. We are sorry that you felt our response was rude. We will address this internally to ensure all customer interactions are handled with courtesy and professionalism.

We wish you all the best in finding a caterer that perfectly suits your needs.

Sincerely,

The Viva Foods Team
reviews/0/text:
Consulted for a small gathering of 10 people for delivery, not catering, buffet or a staffed event. I asked clearly for the menu for some options. Instead, asked me 20 questions about out the gathering, including budget, then once the menu was finally sent, it was based only on # of people not the type or amount of food. I don’t know exactly how many people are coming so I asked if they only price based on number of people that the menu suggests, because i want to order particular items not a set menu based on # of people.

Got the cheekiest response: “if you need the price down just order less food”

Huge time wasters and rather insulting to boot. Ordering from Grab is honestly a better option than working with these clowns. More straightforward and less rudeness

reviews/1/text:
Went to this place for lunch as it’s been recommended by my Japanese colleague who has a huge love with Viet street food. Very fresh ingredients and very tasty soup without (or with very little) MSG, which was a pleasant experience for a Viet who always leave most Hanoi diners with food coma🥹
Plus, super nice owner and staff🥰

- - -
Ngon nhaaaa, ốc tươi giòn tanh tách. Ưng nhất là nước không có (hoặc không có nhiều) bột ngọt. Người của quán ai cũng tử tế niềm nở. Quán không tên Bún Riêu Moi nữa mà là Mr. Ỉn, chỉ cần đi vào con hẻm có một chị ngồi bán giò chả đầu hẻm là tới nhé.

Very fresh ingredients and very tasty soup without (or with very little) MSG, which was a pleasant experience for a Vietnamese who always leaves most Hanoi diners with food coma🥹

- - -
Delicious, fresh and crunchy snails. The best part is that the soup doesn’t have (or doesn’t have much) MSG. Everyone at the restaurant is kind and welcoming. The restaurant is no longer called Bun Rieu Moi but Mr. In, just go into the alley where there is a lady selling ham and sausage at the beginning of the alley and you’ll get there.

reviews/0/text:
✅ +1 trải nghiệm không dám quay lại trừ khi bạn thật sự không còn chỗ để ăn cơm.
Lần đầu nên không biết giá và không thấy để bảng ghi nên nhóm mình hỏi giá phần cơm là bao nhiêu và có phần mực nhìn rất chất lượng nên mình hỏi tiếp vẫn giá 40k đúng không ạ. Có lẽ vì trưa khách đông nên cô bực và nói "có ăn không mà hỏi tới hỏi lui", nhóm mình rén quá nên ord luôn 2 phần bún bò và 1 phần mực. Nhưng khi tụi mình vừa ra bàn ngồi thì nghe thấy bên trong vọng ra, tiếng của chú nói "phần bún bò này của ai đây" và chưa kịp biết là quán tự phục vụ hay không thì cô quát lớn "tụi nó có ăn đâu, tụi nó đi rồi"
Dạ cô ơi, tụi con đứng cách cô có 1 bàn khách đang ngồi ăn thôi. 🥹
➡️Chốt lại 1 buổi ăn: bún bò kiểu miền nam (3 lát bò, 1 cục thịt xương heo, 2 lát chả) có vị nhưng không đậm đà theo kiểu miền Trung, cơm bình thường, được tặng kèo trái cây (1 trái chuối mỗi phần ăn)
✨Hãy thử nếu bạn là người chỉ muốn ăn cơm + biết mình muốn ăn gì trước khi tới quán + không lo về giá
reviews/0/textTranslated:
✅ +1 experience, don't dare to come back unless you really have no place to eat.
The first time so I didn't know the price and didn't see the board so my group asked how much the rice portion was and the squid portion looked very good so I asked again, it was still 40k right. Maybe because there were many customers at noon so the lady was upset and said "are you going to eat or not, why are you asking back and forth", my group was too shy so we ordered 2 beef noodle soup portions and 1 squid portion. But when we just sat down at the table, we heard the voice from inside, the man's voice saying "whose beef noodle soup portion is this?" and before we could know if it was a self-service restaurant or not, she shouted loudly "they didn't eat, they left"
Yes, ma'am, we were standing just 1 table away from you, where customers were eating. 🥹
➡️To conclude a meal: Southern-style beef noodle soup (3 slices of beef, 1 piece of pork bone, 2 slices of ham) has flavor but not as strong as the Central style, normal rice, and a free fruit bowl (1 banana per serving)
✨Try it if you are someone who only wants to eat rice + know what you want to eat before coming to the restaurant + don't worry about the price

reviews/0/text:
In A Nutshell:

-Banh Uot Co Nga is a treasure chest right in the heart of District 1.
-The very kind old lady named Co Nga is a great chef.
-She makes quite possibly the best Banh Cuon that I've ever eaten!
-It's crazy to think she can do it all sitting down on a short plastic chair w/ a rice hat on the busy sidewalk.
-The taste of all the ingredients combine to make your mouth salivate.
-She even refilled my bowl w/ extra pork, basil, noodles & fried garlic.

Overall, she showed me some photos of Vietnamese & international celebrities who also seemed to enjoy this delicious Banh Cuon street food.  I highly recommend stopping by!!!

title: 北海道幸
address: 180a Pasteur, Bến Nghé, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/text:
パスター通りのSushi Hokkaido Sachiに行きました。
店の地下にバイク駐車場があります。
セキュリティはおじさんとお兄さん2人がいました。
店は非常に大きく3階まであり、1階がテーブル席、2〜3階は座敷で300人くらいは座れそうです。
着物姿の若いベトナム女性2人が入り口のドアを開けてくれ「いらっしゃいませ」と出迎えてくれました。
午後8時ごろの予約なしの入店、しばらくお待ち下さいと5分くらい待たされ1階のテーブル席に案内されました。
店内はほぼ客で埋まっているほど繁盛してました。
メニューは驚くほどたくさんあり、選ぶのに時間がかかりました。
ホールスタッフもカウンターの板前も全てベトナム人の若い人達です。
私の席に来たホールスタッフは少し日本語が話せました。
接客態度は非常に良かったです。
私が頼んだ料理は全て美味しく、日本のレベルに達していたので満足できました。
握り寿司は少しかために握られてましたが、美味しくネタは新鮮でした。
値段は安いと思います。
店内は非常に居心地が良く、長居をしてしまいました。
おすすめの店です。

写真は食べてる途中で思い出して撮影したものです。

2019年10月10日
reviews/0/textTranslated:
I went to Sushi Hokkaido Sachi on Pastor Street.

There is a motorcycle parking lot in the basement of the restaurant.

There were an older man and two younger men guarding security.

The restaurant is very large, spanning three floors. The first floor is full of table seating, and the second and third floors are full of tatami rooms, with seating for about 300 people.

Two young Vietnamese women in kimonos opened the entrance door and greeted me with a "Welcome."

I walked in without a reservation around 8pm, and after a five-minute wait, I was shown to a table on the first floor.

The restaurant was so busy that it was almost full of customers.

The menu was surprisingly extensive, and it took me a while to choose.

The wait staff and the chefs at the counter were all young Vietnamese.

The wait staff who attended to my table spoke a little Japanese.

The service was excellent.

All the dishes I ordered were delicious and of Japanese standard, so I was very satisfied.

The nigiri sushi was a little firm, but it was tasty and the ingredients were fresh.
I think the prices are reasonable.
The interior is very comfortable, and I ended up staying for a while.
I highly recommend this restaurant.

I remembered to take this photo halfway through my meal.

October 10, 2019

title: Nhà hàng Nhật Hotto
address: B3-4 Vincom HCM, 45A Lý Tự Trọng, Bến Nghé, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/text:
Hotto là một trong những quán cơm kiểu Nhật mà mình hay ghé khi cần một bữa ăn nhanh nhưng vẫn nóng hổi và đủ chất. Lần gần nhất ghé vào ngày 12/11, quán cực kỳ đông khách nhưng phục vụ vẫn ổn, nhân viên vui vẻ và hỗ trợ khá nhanh. Gần đây Hotto có món mới – sốt kem tiêu, ăn vào thơm béo, mặn vừa và đặc biệt hợp khi trộn cùng cơm nóng.

Món ăn mang ra lúc nào cũng trong tình trạng “xèo xèo” bốc khói nghi ngút, nghe mùi thơm mà hấp dẫn lắm. Nhưng vì quá nóng nên ăn vội là dễ phỏng lưỡi — ai quen kiểu stone bowl chắc hiểu cảm giác này. Nhân viên ở đây thân thiện, nhiệt tình, chỉ tiếc là anh quản lý trước kia rất dễ thương và chăm khách thì dạo này không thấy nữa, chắc anh nghỉ làm rồi, hơi tiếc thật sự.

Tuy nhiên, không phải lần nào trải nghiệm cũng hoàn hảo. Mình từng thử phần US beef 149k kèm trứng nhưng chất lượng thịt hôm đó khá tệ, có mùi như thịt để lâu, ăn không nổi quá 2 miếng. Hy vọng quán kiểm soát chất lượng nguyên liệu tốt hơn.

Hotto nhìn chung hợp để ăn trưa nhanh cùng bạn bè hoặc đồng nghiệp: giá ổn, suất ăn no, tiện lợi. Nhưng một điểm trừ lớn là mùi đồ ăn bám vào quần áo mỗi khi bước vào quán — gần như lần nào ăn tại chỗ cũng bị. Vì vậy, nhiều lúc mình muốn gọi về cho tiện, nhưng đồ ăn giao về lại không còn nóng xèo xèo như ăn tại chỗ.

Tóm lại, Hotto có món ngon, giá hợp lý và phục vụ ổn. Nếu họ cải thiện chất lượng thịt và vấn đề mùi bám quần áo, trải nghiệm chắc chắn sẽ hoàn hảo hơn nhiều.
reviews/0/textTranslated:
Hotto is one of the Japanese-style rice restaurants that I often visit when I need a quick but still hot and nutritious meal. The last time I visited was on November 12, the restaurant was extremely crowded but the service was still good, the staff were cheerful and helpful quite quickly. Recently, Hotto has a new dish - pepper cream sauce, which is fragrant and fatty, just salty enough and especially good when mixed with hot rice. 

The food is always brought out in a "sizzling" state, steaming, the smell is very attractive. But because it is too hot, eating it in a hurry can easily burn your tongue - anyone who is used to stone bowl style will understand this feeling. The staff here are friendly and enthusiastic, it's just a pity that the previous manager who was very cute and attentive to customers is no longer seen these days, he must have quit his job, it's a real pity. 

However, not every experience is perfect. I tried the 149k US beef with egg but the quality of the meat that day was quite bad, it smelled like old meat, I couldn't eat more than 2 pieces. Hopefully the restaurant can control the quality of the ingredients better.

Hotto is generally suitable for a quick lunch with friends or colleagues: reasonable price, full meal, convenient. But a big minus point is that the smell of food sticks to clothes every time you enter the restaurant - almost every time I eat at the restaurant. Therefore, many times I want to order takeout for convenience, but the food delivered is not as hot as eating at the restaurant.

In short, Hotto has delicious food, reasonable prices and good service. If they improve the quality of meat and the smell problem on clothes, the experience will definitely be much more perfect.

reviews/0/text:
日本人街レタントンの近くにあり、日本のホームセンターそのままの感覚で利用できる便利なお店。日用品から工具、生活雑貨まで幅広く揃っていて、旅行中に“ちょっと必要になったもの”を調達するのにとても助かる。

店内は明るく、商品も見やすく整理されていて、日本基準の品質がそのまま並んでいる安心感が大きい。洗濯用品、キッチンアイテム、文房具、掃除用品など、ローカル店では見つけづらい“日本式の使いやすいもの”が手に入るのが魅力。

価格も日本よりやや安め〜同程度で、クオリティを考えるとコスパ良し。
スタッフも親切で、英語対応にも慣れているため買い物がスムーズ。

レタントン周辺の
・ユニクロ
・無印良品
・ダイソー
などと合わせて周れる、日本ブランドがまとまった便利エリアの一角。

旅行中の細かな困りごとを解決できる“日本人にとってありがたいホームセンター”です。
reviews/0/textTranslated:
Located near the Japanese town of Le Thanh Ton, this convenient store feels just like a home improvement center in Japan. With a wide selection of items, from daily necessities to tools and household goods, it's extremely helpful for sourcing those "little necessities" while traveling.

The store is bright, the products are clearly organized, and the quality is guaranteed to be up to Japanese standards. The appeal is the availability of "Japanese-style, easy-to-use" items that are hard to find in local stores, such as laundry supplies, kitchen items, stationery, and cleaning supplies.

Prices are slightly cheaper or comparable to those in Japan, making it good value for money considering the quality.

The friendly staff are accustomed to speaking English, making shopping a breeze.

This convenient area, home to many Japanese brands, is perfect for exploring nearby Le Thanh Ton, including:
Uniqlo
MUJI
Daiso

This "home improvement center for Japanese people" can solve any little trouble you might have while traveling.

title: Golden Dynasty PEKING DUCK Vincom Đồng Khởi
address: 72 Lê Thánh Tôn, Phường Sài Gòn, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh 700000, Vietnam
reviews/0/text:
Lần đầu tiên đi ăn 1 quán Trung mà cảm thấy như đi xin cảm giác khó tả địa điểm Vincom Đồng Khởi tầm 19h ngày 22 tháng 11. Ngồi đợi order lâu mà chị mặc áo trắng cứ báo là cần gì làm kêu bạn khác qua hỗ trợ, cứ thúc dục bạn đi kiểu ko cần hỗ trợ. Gọi đồ ăn 7 món nhưng thời điểm 19h đó cái gì cũng hết thật khó hiểu chỉ có 3 món là còn, Đồ ăn ra chén đũa cũng không 1 ái set up (Coi tấm
Hình thì thấy vị trí ăn của mình cũng hiểu là chả được hỗ trợ và bố trí phần thảm chén để gác đũa và muỗng để đảm vệ sinh) liện chén đũa ra mình tự phân phát như cơm gia đình, xin mấy cái thìa thì mỗi lần đưa 1 cái, và đưa 2 lần cho 2 cái khác nhau / 4 người, Đồ ăn thì tạm ( được món vịt nướng ăn tạm ổn) còn lại thì rất bình thường. Quán quá tệ ăn 1 lần sẽ không dám ghé lần 2 không vì giá đắc mà sợ cảm giác bị coi thường.
reviews/0/textTranslated: The first time I went to a Chinese restaurant, I felt like I was begging for something, an indescribable feeling at Vincom Dong Khoi, around 7pm on November 22. I waited for a long time to order, but the woman in white kept saying that she needed something to do, asking other people to come over and help, and kept urging me to go as if I didn't need any help. I ordered 7 dishes, but at 7pm everything was gone, it was really confusing, only 3 dishes were left. The food was served with bowls and chopsticks, and no one set it up (Looking at the photo, I saw that my eating position also meant that there was no support and a mat was set up to rest chopsticks and spoons to ensure hygiene). I took out bowls and chopsticks and distributed them myself like a family meal. I asked for a few spoons, but each time I was given one, and I gave them twice for 2 different ones / 4 people. The food was okay (the grilled duck dish was okay), the rest was very normal. The restaurant was so bad, I ate once and wouldn't dare to come back a second time, not because of the expensive price but because of the feeling of being looked down upon.
reviews/1/text: nhân viên phục vụ theo trải nghiệm không thật sự tốt, thái độ ko tốt, đồ ăn cũng ko quá nổi bật, ngoại trừ Vịt thì có phần OK hơn các món còn lại, món rau rửa chế biến khá bẩn mà cũng đem ra phục vụ khách.
reviews/1/textTranslated: The service staff experience is not really good, attitude is not good, food is not outstanding, except for the duck which is better than the rest, the vegetable dish is quite dirty and still served to customers.
reviews/2/text:
food wise, above expectations.

service staff, all depend upon individual encounters. for us, everyone knows their duty and service is just right.. after all, at one glance. the service staffs are just that few.. so delay or no service is inevitable..

overall dining area outlook, it is just normal. waiting time expected for walk-in during peak hours.

reviews/0/text: Very extensive menu. I ordered the shrimp and it was really good. I just forgot I was in another country and didn't expect the heads to be on the skewers. reviews/1/text: Cibo ottimo personale gentile e servizio rapido, lo consiglio
reviews/1/textTranslated: Excellent food, friendly staff and fast service, I recommend it
reviews/2/text: Это было ужасно, невкусно, некачествнно, неоправданно дорого. Ожидал полчаса . Официант потребовал заказать две порции. Суп и основное блюдо принесли одновременно. Рисовая бумага для роллов была несъедобная и твердая. Оказалось, ее нужно было вымачивать в воде . Официант уже после рассчета (чаевые , 8 процентов сразу включают в счет ) сказал , что была очень занята и не смогла принести воду. Суп - огромная лоханка соленой воды, в которой плавали креветки.  Это был с большим отрывом худший ресторан за 2 месяца во Вьетнаме . Еще и столы неуютные , один на 5 разных гостей . Просто ужасно
reviews/2/textTranslated: It was awful, tasteless, poor quality, unreasonably expensive. I waited for half an hour. The waiter demanded to order two portions. The soup and the main course were brought at the same time. The rice paper for the rolls was inedible and hard. It turned out that it had to be soaked in water. The waiter, after calculating (tips, 8 percent are immediately included in the bill), said that she was very busy and could not bring water. The soup was a huge bowl of salt water with shrimps floating in it. This was by far the worst restaurant in 2 months in Vietnam. The tables were also uncomfortable, one for 5 different guests. Just awful.

title: Nhà hàng Chả cá 36

reviews/1/text:

Chảo thì nấu mãi vẫn chưa sôi, đem đi hâm lại thì đem ra chảo bẩn.Tóm lại chưa bàn đến đồ ăn ngon không nhưng cần cải thiện chất lượng phục vụ.
Ps: mẹ mình ăn và kêu đồ ăn ngon, hợp gu miền trung và miền bắc. Mình thì thấy cũng đc, cũng bth
reviews/1/textTranslated: Went to eat at a restaurant in Vincom Binh Thanh. Really disappointed. Not to mention the lack of food, there were only 2 staff. When I called for service, they didn't listen, and when I called, they frowned (the higher-ranking staff was more polite), but this also made my dining experience really bad. The food was brought out without a ladle or spoon, and when it was brought out, the ladle was dirty... really bad. The pan was still boiling after a long time of cooking, and when I reheated it, the pan was dirty. In short, let's not talk about whether the food was delicious or not, but the service quality needs to be improved. Ps: my mother ate and said the food was delicious, suitable for the taste of the central and northern regions. I think it's okay, normal
reviews/2/text:
Lần đầu tiên ăn một quán lẩu mà phải mua thêm 1 phần rau 30k nhưng chỉ loe nghoe có mấy cọng rau. 2 phần bún 19k nhỏ xíu.  1 phần lẩu 299k ăn không ra gì. Nước lẩu phải nói là KINH KHỦNG của KINH KHỦNG.  QUÁ TỞM !!!!!! Ngồi đợi 1 nồi lẩu 30p chỉ để ngồi đợi cá được cắt ra bày biện trên khay đá. Để làm gì vậy ? Trong khi cá sẽ được bỏ vô nồi lẩu mà, bày biện làm chi ? Hay phần đó chiếm 200k còn lẩu thì chỉ 99k thôi ????? Đây là một trải nghiệm rất khủng khiếp. Một nồi lẩu KINH TỞM
Nếu quán chỉ có thể lừa ngta đc 1 lần thì làm ơn nấu sao cho dễ ăn một chút.
Nhắc trước mn đừng đến quán này ăn
Cho 1 sao còn thấy uổng
Bái phục quán 🙏🙏🙏
reviews/2/textTranslated:
The first time I ate at a hot pot restaurant, I had to buy an extra 30k vegetable portion but it only had a few stems. 2 small 19k noodle portions. 1 299k hot pot portion was not good at all. The hot pot broth was HORRIBLE of HORRIBLE. TOO DISGUSTING !!!!!! I waited for a hot pot for 30 minutes just to wait for the fish to be cut and arranged on an ice tray. For what? When the fish will be put in the hot pot, why arrange it? Or that portion takes up 200k while the hot pot is only 99k ????? This was a terrible experience. A DISGUSTING hot pot
If the restaurant can only fool people once, please cook it so it's easier to eat.
I warn everyone not to come to this restaurant
Giving 1 star is still a waste
I admire the restaurant 🙏🙏🙏

title: Mutsumian Omakase & Sukiyaki

reviews/0/text:
Mutsumian nằm trên tầng 5 của 1 toà gồm nhiều nhà hàng ramen, izakaza
Không gian nhỏ nhắn ấm cúng view khá đẹp, counter ngồi đc khoảng 10nguoi xung quanh chef khá ổn, sạch sẽ gọn gàng
Menu khá ổn áp , giá cũng hợp lý, gan cá chày sốt ponzu ăn khá khô đối với mình nhưng 3 loai sashimi thì rất tươi, bò wagu a5 mềm tan trong miệng nhưng k nên chấm với muối vì khá mặn, chef còn tặng thêm món cho cả gia đình, và các bạn nv tặng thêm nướng izakaza ăn khá ngon ( cùng 1 chủ trên lầu 6)
Bánh sinh nhật cá hồi cá ngừ khá tươi và ăn rất ngon
Nếu bạn iu thích omakase thì mutsumian la 1 điểm đến lý tưởng , có kể ket hop alacarte và sukiyaki
reviews/0/textTranslated:
Mutsumian is located on the 5th floor of a building with many ramen and izakaza restaurants
The space is small and cozy with a nice view, the counter can seat about 10 people around, the chef is quite good, clean and tidy
The menu is quite good, the price is also reasonable, the ponzu-sauced monkfish liver is quite dry for me but the 3 types of sashimi are very fresh, the a5 wagu beef is soft and melts in your mouth but you shouldn't dip it with salt because it's quite salty, the chef also gives away extra dishes for the whole family, and the staff also gives away grilled izakaza which is quite delicious (same owner on the 6th floor)
The tuna and salmon birthday cake is quite fresh and delicious
If you love omakase, mutsumian is an ideal destination, including alacarte and sukiyaki combinations

title: Singapore Frog Leg Resturant
address: 27 Đông Du, Bến Nghé, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh 70000, Vietnam
reviews/0/text:
這是一家讓人一吃就會想再回訪的好店！
田雞非常新鮮、肉質軟嫩，醬汁香氣濃郁又下飯，配上熱騰騰的砂鍋粥，真的會一口接一口停不下來！

我們也點了幾道配菜，每一道都令人驚喜：
• 砂鍋田雞——香氣十足、調味恰到好處，非常入味。
• 招牌白粥——綿滑順口，是最療癒的 comfort food。
• 清炒空心菜——香辣帶勁，風味非常好。
• 炸金針菇——超級酥脆，搭配醬料超好吃！
• 春捲 & 炸雞——外酥內嫩，份量也很足，吃起來非常滿足。

所有料理都現做上桌、熱騰騰又香味十足，份量大、味道道地。
服務人員也非常親切貼心，讓整體用餐體驗更完美。

非常推薦給喜歡田雞煲、砂鍋粥或是想和朋友家人好好吃一餐的人。
我一定還會再來！❤️🍲🐸

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Absolutely amazing Singapore frog leg restaurant!

I had an unforgettable dining experience here!
The frog legs were incredibly fresh, tender, and full of flavor — cooked perfectly in a rich claypot sauce that paired beautifully with the smooth, comforting porridge. Every bite was addictive!

We also ordered several side dishes, and each one exceeded expectations:
• Claypot frog legs – fragrant, savory, and perfectly seasoned.
• Signature porridge – silky, warm, and the best comfort food after a long day.
• Stir-fried morning glory – flavorful with just the right amount of spice.
• Crispy shredded mushrooms – super crunchy and delicious with the dipping sauce!
• Spring rolls & fried chicken – crispy on the outside, juicy on the inside. Absolutely satisfying!

The food came out hot and freshly cooked, portions were generous, and the flavors were authentic.
Service was friendly and attentive, making the entire experience even better.

Highly recommend this place if you love frog leg claypot, comfort food, or simply want a great meal with friends and family. I will definitely be coming back! ❤️🍲🐸

We also ordered several side dishes, and each one was a delightful surprise:

• Signature White Congee – smooth and creamy, the most comforting food.

• Stir-fried Water Spinach – spicy and flavorful, with a fantastic taste.

• Fried Enoki Mushrooms – super crispy, and delicious with the sauce!

All dishes are freshly made and served piping hot and fragrant, with generous portions and authentic flavors.

The service staff are also very friendly and attentive, making the overall dining experience even more perfect.

Highly recommended for anyone who loves frog stew, congee, or wants to enjoy a delicious meal with friends and family. I will definitely come again! ❤️🍲🐸

title: Nhà hàng Isyo isyo
address: Thái Văn Lung, Bến Nghé, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/text:
​"A masterclass in charcoal grilling. 🍢
​I’ve tried many Japanese spots in Vietnam, but Issho stands out for its attention to detail. You can tell they use high-quality ingredients. The menu explains their unique salt blend (a mix of Vietnamese and Japanese salt), and it really makes a difference on the skewers—bringing out the natural flavors of the meat without being overpowering.
​We tried the Horse Meat Sashimi (Basashi), which is a rare find in HCMC. It was incredibly fresh, tender, and served with the proper condiments. The Raw Chicken Bowl with egg yolk was creamy and rich—a must-try for sashimi lovers.
​The open kitchen layout lets you watch the chefs at work, which adds to the trust and experience. Service was attentive without being intrusive.
​Verdict: Top-tier food quality in a relaxed setting. Perfect for a casual dinner date or solo dining at the counter. Don't skip the Sapporo beer; the pour is excellent with a perfect foam head. 10/10 will return. 🥢"

reviews/0/text: Dịch vụ rất tệ. Nhiều lần vào mua, giá trên kệ khác với giá khi tính tiền. Thắc mắc thì nhân viên cũng giả vờ kiểm tra... và báo do nhầm lẫn, rồi treo giá khuyến mãi nhưng khi tính tiền thì không áp khuyến mãi, nhân viên giải thích ấp úng , lấp liếm. Trị giá nhỏ nhưng cung cách giống như đang lừa dối nhau. Vì không phải 1 lần, mà rất nhiều lần nên mình mới kết luận như vậy. Các bạn cứ thử để ý khi mua ở snack kingdom xem có đúng không.
reviews/0/textTranslated: The service is very bad. Many times when I went to buy, the price on the shelf was different from the price when paying. When I asked, the staff pretended to check... and said it was a mistake, then posted the promotional price but when paying, the promotion was not applied, the staff explained hesitantly and evaded. The value was small but the way they acted was like they were deceiving each other. Because it happened not once, but many times, that's why I came to that conclusion. You guys should try to pay attention when buying at Snack Kingdom to see if it's true.

address: Vincom Center, Lê Thánh Tôn/72 Đồng Khởi, Bến Nghé, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/text: Sehr schwierig zu finden, im 3. UG einer Shopping Mall. Sehr touristisches Angebot, was hier als Vorteil erwähnt werden soll. Lange Wartezeit an Kasse.
reviews/0/textTranslated: Very difficult to find, located on the third basement level of a shopping mall. Very touristy selection, which should be mentioned as an advantage. Long wait at the checkout.
reviews/1/text:
お土産を買うのにお薦めなスーパーマーケット。店内はそこまで広くないものの、コーヒーやフォー、調味料など、お土産として欲しいものは全てここで揃いました。
大きな商業施設の地下3階(レストランフロア)に位置していますが、フロアの最も端に有り、とにかく入り口がわかりづらいです。(地下3階のフロアをぐるぐると2周してしまい、近くのお店の店員さんに場所を尋ねるほどです。)HIGHLAND COFFEEやKOI THEを目指して歩くと容易に見つけることができると思います。
reviews/1/textTranslated:
This supermarket is recommended for buying souvenirs. The store isn't particularly large, but it has everything you need as a souvenir, including coffee, pho, and condiments. 
It's located on the third basement floor (restaurant floor) of a large commercial facility, but it's at the very end of the floor, so the entrance is quite difficult to find. (I ended up walking around the third basement floor twice and asking a staff member at a nearby store for directions.) If you walk towards HIGHLAND COFFEE and KOI THE, you should be able to find it easily.
reviews/2/text:
Winmart you’ve got to fix the design/layout of your checkout area. The check-out experience was much better before your recent remodel.

The position of the check-out counters against the wall creates a setup where nobody knows where to line up. When customers finish paying, they’re basically trapped in the middle of a crowd of people waiting to pay and getting past everyone is awkward. The check out counters themselves are much worse than the old design which had conveyor belts - the new counters require everyone to bend far forward over another rack of products, making placing/retrieving products awkward/uncomfortable. The “check out” sign on the ceiling is not a good idea either, the sign should be perpendicular to the floor not parallel with it - nobody notices a sign that’s not readable until you’re directly under it looking straight up.

title: Nhà Hàng Hoa Mai
address: 141 Nguyễn Huệ, Bến Nghé, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/1/text:
Tôi vừa có dịp trải nghiệm tại một nhà hàng thật sự để lại nhiều ấn tượng khó quên. Ngay từ lúc bước vào, không gian đã mang lại cảm giác ấm cúng và sang trọng với ánh đèn vàng dịu, bàn ghế được sắp xếp tinh tế, vừa đảm bảo sự riêng tư vừa tạo cảm giác thoải mái. Nhân viên phục vụ cực kỳ chuyên nghiệp, luôn nở nụ cười thân thiện và sẵn sàng hỗ trợ khách từ việc chọn món đến gợi ý loại đồ uống phù hợp.

Về món ăn, phải nói là tinh tế từ cách trình bày đến hương vị. Từng món đều được chăm chút tỉ mỉ, nguyên liệu tươi ngon, gia vị nêm nếm hài hòa khiến thực khách vừa nhìn đã muốn thử ngay. Đặc biệt, phần bếp chú trọng cân bằng giữa hương vị truyền thống và phong cách hiện đại, tạo nên sự độc đáo riêng không dễ tìm thấy ở nơi khác.

Giá cả cũng rất hợp lý so với chất lượng nhận được. Bạn không chỉ được thưởng thức bữa ăn ngon miệng mà còn được trải nghiệm một dịch vụ hoàn hảo, xứng đáng để quay lại nhiều lần. Đây thực sự là địa điểm lý tưởng để gặp gỡ bạn bè, sum họp gia đình hay tổ chức những buổi hẹn đặc biệt.
reviews/1/textTranslated:
I just had the opportunity to experience a restaurant that really left an unforgettable impression. Right from the moment I entered, the space brought a cozy and luxurious feeling with soft yellow lights, tables and chairs were delicately arranged, ensuring privacy while creating a sense of comfort. The service staff was extremely professional, always smiling friendly and ready to assist customers from choosing dishes to suggesting suitable drinks. 

Regarding the food, it must be said that it is sophisticated from the presentation to the taste. Each dish is meticulously cared for, fresh ingredients, harmonious seasonings make diners want to try it right away. In particular, the kitchen focuses on balancing traditional flavors and modern style, creating a uniqueness that is not easy to find elsewhere. 

The price is also very reasonable compared to the quality received. You not only enjoy a delicious meal but also experience perfect service, worthy of coming back many times. This is truly an ideal place to meet friends, family reunions or organize special dates.

reviews/0/text: A truly hidden gem in Saigon. Every dishes is flavorful. Even the supposedly bland soup taste better than other Com Xuat or Com Binh Dan style restaurant I ever ate in Hanoi and Saigon. The rice is also of higher quality. The free iced tea is also taste better than others. The mother is also friendly.
reviews/1/responseFromOwnerText: ご来店ありがとうございました。
reviews/1/text:
魚、肉、野菜、気分で選べる逸品料理。
日本人好みの甘すぎない味付けで、どれもこれも美味しくて迷う。ご飯たっぷり（調整可能）付け合わせ野菜にスープ付き。
1品で4〜50kvnd、2品だと50kvnd〜。
お母さんの優しい笑顔の安心感、日本語できるスタッフもいます。

11時くらいがその日の料理がズラリ20種類〜並びます。ランチタイムはベトナム人でわんさか。相席です。
1時過ぎると、品数ぐんと減りますね。
家庭的な味が欲しくなったらココ！
reviews/1/textTranslated:
Choose from a variety of exquisite dishes, including fish, meat, and vegetables, depending on your mood.
The not-too-sweet seasoning is to Japanese liking, and everything is so delicious it's hard to choose. The portion is generous (adjustable), with side vegetables and soup.
One dish is 40-50kVND, and two dishes start from 50kVND.
The mother's kind smile is reassuring, and some staff speak Japanese.

Around 11am, they line up over 20 different dishes of the day. It's packed with Vietnamese people at lunchtime, and you'll have to share tables.
The selection of dishes decreases significantly after 1pm.
If you're craving a home-style meal, this is the place to go!
reviews/2/responseFromOwnerText:
Hương Quán xin cảm ơn quý khách đã đến và ủng hộ quán. Quán sẽ cố gắng hoàn thiện và chỉnh chu hơn, mong quý khách sẽ tiếp tục ủng hộ quán.
Xin chân thành cảm ơn quý khách!

reviews/0/text:
Great Experience at Qui Mixology Pub!

I had an amazing time at Qui Mixology Pub. The atmosphere was lively, and the DJ kept the energy perfect throughout the night. The food was surprisingly good, and what really stood out was the thoughtful gesture from the house—offering complimentary food vouchers for each table. Such a unique and fun idea for groups!

The staff were all wonderful, with excellent customer service from start to finish. The front door team was especially courteous and welcoming, setting a great tone for the evening.

Overall, Qui Mixology Pub exceeded my expectations. Highly recommended for a fun night out with great vibes, good food, and fantastic service!

title: Yumme Food & Drinks
address: 31A Nguyễn Bỉnh Khiêm, Bến Nghé, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/text:
Dạo gần đây tôi hay ghé nghỉ chân tại Yumme Food & Drink ở số 31 Nguyễn Bỉnh Khiêm, Quận 1 và thật sự bất ngờ với trải nghiệm tại quán. Không gian nhỏ nhưng sạch sẽ, gọn gàng, tạo cảm giác thân thiện ngay từ khi bước vào. Điều làm tôi ấn tượng nhất chính là món nước ép cóc muối tôm chỉ 35k nhưng lại cực kỳ ngon và độc đáo. Vị cóc chua dịu hoà với độ mặn nhẹ của muối và chút cay thơm của tôm rim khiến thức uống vừa lạ miệng vừa kích thích vị giác. Uống một ngụm là cảm nhận được sự tươi mới, đậm đà nhưng không hề gắt hay quá ngọt, rất hợp với những ngày nắng nóng ở Sài Gòn.
Ông bà chủ kiêm pha chế, kiêm phục vụ rất dễ thương, vui vẻ nhanh nhẹn và khá nhiệt tình. Dù quán đông vào giờ cao điểm nhưng đồ uống được chuẩn bị khá nhanh, không phải chờ đợi lâu. Giá cả so với khu vực trung tâm như Quận 1 thì phải nói là quá hợp lý. Tôi nghĩ đây là địa điểm rất đáng để thử, đặc biệt với ai yêu thích các loại nước ép có hương vị sáng tạo. Chắc chắn
reviews/0/textTranslated: Recently, I often stop by Yumme Food & Drink at 31 Nguyen Binh Khiem, District 1 and was really surprised with the experience at the shop. The space is small but clean, tidy, creating a friendly feeling right from the moment I entered. What impressed me most was the tamarind juice with shrimp salt, only 35k but extremely delicious and unique. The sour taste of tamarind mixed with the slight saltiness of salt and a bit of spicy aroma of braised shrimp makes the drink both strange and stimulating to the taste buds. Taking a sip, you can feel the freshness, richness but not too harsh or too sweet, very suitable for hot days in Saigon. The owners who are also bartenders and servers are very cute, cheerful, quick and quite enthusiastic. Although the shop is crowded during peak hours, the drinks are prepared quite quickly, without having to wait long. The price compared to central areas like District 1 is very reasonable. I think this is a place worth trying, especially for those who love creatively flavored juices. Definitely
reviews/1/text:
Nước ép ổi ở đây ngon nha mn, ngọt vừa vị, dậy mùi ổi tươi, oder quán mới cắt ổi ép nên vị kiểu rất tươi luôn ấy, anh chị chủ rất nice, nói chuyện nhỏ nhẹ vui vẻ phục vụ khách, đến đây dùng nước cảm giác được trân trọng
Có chỗ để xe phía trc vỉa hè, có toilet phía sau sạch sẽ, wifi mạnh

There is a parking space in front of the sidewalk, there is a clean toilet in the back, strong wifi

Speaking of tacos, I wish they were a little larger.

title: Canh bún Mạc Đĩnh Chi
address: QMMX+PXW, Mạc Đĩnh Chi, Đa Kao, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/text: Ngon, rẻ, chất lượng, nước dùng đậm đà topping bao la mà chỉ 25k tô như hình
reviews/0/textTranslated: Delicious, cheap, quality, rich broth, lots of toppings for only 25k bowl as pictured
reviews/1/text:
Tô canh bún rất hợp vị, hấp dẫn và kèm nhiều topping. Nước dùng có màu đỏ cam nhẹ, đậm đà, được nấu từ cua đồng. Bún to, trắng, mềm và mịn. Trên mặt tô là hàng loạt nguyên liệu phong phú như:
•	Rau muống chần xanh mướt, tươi ngon
•	Huyết heo cắt vuông, mềm mịn
•	Chả cua béo, dai, thơm mùi cua
•	Đậu hũ chiên vàng giòn
•	Một ít ốc và nấm rơm
•	Hành lá, rau răm và một muỗng sate ớt tỏi cho vị cay nồng

Tô canh bún này mang đậm chất dân dã miền Nam.

Quán ăn vỉa hè, nhiều dân văn phòng hay đến ăn sáng. Giá rẻ mà còn nhiều nữa.
reviews/1/textTranslated:
The noodle soup is very tasty, attractive and has many toppings. The broth is light orange-red, rich, and cooked from field crabs. The noodles are big, white, soft and smooth. On top of the bowl are a series of rich ingredients such as:
• Fresh, green, blanched water spinach
• Soft, square-cut pig's blood
• Fatty, chewy crab cakes with a crab aroma
• Crispy fried tofu
• A few snails and straw mushrooms
• Scallions, Vietnamese coriander and a spoonful of chili-garlic satay for a spicy taste

This noodle soup has a rustic Southern feel.

Sidewalk eatery, many office workers often come here for breakfast. Cheap and also a lot.

reviews/0/textTranslated:

reviews/0/text:
Quán bún bò núp hẻm ở đầu đường Nguyễn Đình Chiểu, khúc đường kẹp giữa của Hoàng Sa và Nguyễn Bỉnh Khiêm. Quán nhỏ gọn, khiêm tốn với 3 chiếc bàn, 1 tủ đồ ăn và 2 nồi nước lèo.

Lần đầu đến đây nhưng mình gặp toàn khách ăn quen, nói chuyện rôm rả với chị chủ.
- Nước lèo đậm đà, đa dạng hương vị. Bạn nào dị ứng bột ngọt thì cẩn thận đừng húp nhiều nước lèo nhé.
- Nguyên liệu toppings gồm nạm và chả. Mình thấy trong tủ có cả gân bò.
- Mình gọi 1 tô bún nạm (40K) thịt cắt dày, thơm ngon, hầm mềm vừa tới. Tới tô nào chị chủ mới cắt thịt cho tô đó, nên không hề bị khô.

Quán chỉ có chị chủ và con gái phục vụ, nhưng khá nhanh, đợi tầm 5-10 phút là có món. Trà đá miễn phí.
reviews/0/textTranslated:
A bun bo restaurant hidden in the alley at the beginning of Nguyen Dinh Chieu Street, the street between Hoang Sa and Nguyen Binh Khiem. The restaurant is compact and modest with 3 tables, 1 food cabinet and 2 pots of broth. 

It was my first time here but I met all the regular customers, chatting animatedly with the owner. 

- The broth is rich and has a variety of flavors. If you are allergic to MSG, be careful not to drink too much broth. 

The toppings include brisket and sausage. I saw beef tendon in the cabinet. 

I ordered a bowl of bun bo (40K) with thick, delicious meat, stewed to just the right tenderness. The owner cuts the meat for each bowl, so it is not dry at all. 

The restaurant only has the owner and her daughter serving, but it is quite fast, waiting about 5-10 minutes for the dish. Free iced tea.
reviews/1/text: Chị chủ quán dễ thương, đồ ăn siu ngon, quán ruột của tụi tui
reviews/1/textTranslated: The owner is cute, the food is delicious, our favorite restaurant.

reviews/0/text: Đã từng ăn ở đây nhiều lần rồi. Cũng biết trong nên của quán có bỏ giá đỗ. Nên Hnay tới ăn quán báo chỉ còn 1 bún chả và bún nem thôi. Nhưng quán ép tụi mình nhận chứ nhất quyết không cho trả món. 1 bún chả, 1 bún nem, 1 trà đá và 1 CoCa hết 240k. Thề không bao giờ đặt chân tới quán này. Chả biết là nhân viên hay chủ nhưng thái độ lắm luôn
reviews/0/textTranslated: I have eaten here many times. I also know that the restaurant has bean sprouts in the floor. So today when I went to eat, the restaurant said that there was only 1 bun cha and bun nem left. I was planning not to eat anymore, but I had already come in so I sat down and told the restaurant not to put bean sprouts in because I was allergic. But when the nem was brought out to me, there were still bean sprouts, and the vegetables also had a lot of bean sprouts. But the restaurant forced us to accept it and absolutely did not let us return the dish. 1 bun cha, 1 bun nem, 1 iced tea and 1 CoCa, totaled 240k. I swear I will never set foot in this restaurant again. I don't know if it was the staff or the owner but their attitude was terrible.

Phần bún thì cho nước rất ít, quán ở gần mình nhưng ship tới thì nước dùng nguội rồi. Cho Ít rau, mình ăn mấy quán bún riêu HN rồi thì thấy quán này không phải vị HN.
Đồ ăn trong bún mình thấy không tươi, cảm giác đậu hũ hơi chua nhẹ, cục chả gì đó cũng hơi chua nhẹ bên trong. Được cái giò tai ăn tạm được. Nhưng mà mình ăn cục mọc mình thấy có mùi gián, ớn quá bỏ ko ăn nữa luôn.
1 phần cũng không rẻ lắm á, mua trên app cỡ 50k trở lên tuỳ món
reviews/0/textTranslated:
I ordered 2 portions on Grab: 1 Hanoi old vermicelli soup and 1 crab vermicelli soup.
The vermicelli portion was given very little water, the restaurant is near me but when it was delivered, the broth was cold. The vegetables were given less, I have eaten at several Hanoi vermicelli soup restaurants and found that this one does not have the Hanoi flavor.
The food in the vermicelli was not fresh, the tofu felt a bit sour, the meatloaf was also a bit sour inside. The ear knuckle was edible. But when I ate the meatloaf, I found it smelled like cockroaches, it was so disgusting that I stopped eating it.
1 portion is not that cheap, buying on the app costs around 50k or more depending on the dish

reviews/1/text:
Mình mua rồi chuyển khoản cho chị, chị chưa bật loa thông báo, ngân hàng CỦA CHỊ không vô tiền, mình đã chuyển khoản 2 lần và tự gọi điện ngân hàng để báo về việc này, nhấn mạnh là mình giải quyết với ngân hàng chứ không nói gì chị. Ngân hàng báo sẽ báo chị ấy về khoản double này. Mấy hôm sau ra mua hàng, chồng chị có nói về khoản tiền này và kêu trả lại cho mình, mình đã không định đòi rồi nhưng chị sùng máu la làng lên kêu "chị từ đó giờ chưa quỵt của ai", chửi rủa khách xong kêu "có tiền mặt rồi hẵn mua nha em".
Oke chị, e có tiền mặt nhưng mà e mua chỗ khác
Chúc chị bán được quài quài để có tiền đi sửa cái nết nha chị
reviews/1/textTranslated:
I bought it and transferred the money to her, she didn't turn on the speaker to announce, HER bank didn't have any money, I transferred the money twice and called the bank myself to report this, emphasizing that I would deal with the bank and not say anything to her. The bank said they would report this double amount to her. A few days later, when I went to buy the goods, her husband talked about this amount and asked me to return it to him, I didn't intend to ask for it but she was so angry that she yelled "I've never cheated anyone", cursed the customer and said "I'll buy it when I have cash".
Okay, I have cash but I'll buy it elsewhere
I wish you continued sales so you can have money to fix your character

reviews/1/text:
Chả hiểu quán làm ăn kiểu gì, giờ giấc không rõ ràng. Thứ bảy đến vào lúc 11h thì đóng cửa, trong khi ghi mở cửa từ 8h. Nhắn tin cho nhân viên trên instagram thì không bao giờ thấy trả lời.
Lần khác đi thì tgian quán làm bánh khá lâu, bảo đợi 10-15p mà chắc phải nửa tiếng mới có bánh.
reviews/1/textTranslated: I don't understand how the shop operates, the hours are unclear. On Saturday, it closed at 11am, while it says it opens at 8am. I messaged the staff on Instagram and never got a reply. The other time I went, the shop took a long time to make the cake, they said to wait 10-15 minutes but it took half an hour for the cake to arrive.
reviews/2/text: Đặt đơn trên ShopeeFood thanh toán trước đầy đủ mà quán không chịu làm đơn. Tài xế đầu tới đợi mà không có đơn, gọi quán không chịu bắt máy, cuối cùng không có đơn nên mình phải tự nhắn cho bên tổng đài là không nhận được để hủy. Tài xế 2 tới lúc này là trễ hơn giờ giao dự kiến 35 phút rồi mà quán vẫn chưa làm đơn của mình. ShopeeFood huỷ đơn mà note do tài xế chưa giao, tính ra tội mấy anh tại lỗi hoàn toàn tại shop.
reviews/2/textTranslated: I placed an order on ShopeeFood and paid in full in advance but the restaurant refused to process the order. The first driver came and waited but had no order, called the restaurant but they refused to answer, finally there was no order so I had to text the operator myself that I did not receive it to cancel. The second driver arrived 35 minutes later than the expected delivery time but the restaurant still had not processed my order. ShopeeFood canceled the order but noted that the driver had not delivered yet, so it was entirely the shop's fault.

reviews/1/text:
Quán mở cửa từ t2-t6 : 6h30-13h30 (t7-cn nghỉ)
Mì quảng 55k/ phần thập cẩm tôm gà heo gồm trà (atiso) bán từ sáng tới trưa, nhiều hôm quán hết sớm , nên đi sáng trước giờ trưa, đỡ đông và còn món.
Cơm trưa văn phòng bán khung giờ 11g-13g30 giá 45k/ phần gồm cả cơm + canh + đồ xào + món mặn (ngồi ở quán được phục vụ trà đá free) . Thực đơn ng ày 8 món và thay đổi mỗi ngày, có thể kết bạn zalo cô chủ quán để order giao tới, đỡ ngồi chờ và tránh hết món yêu thích
reviews/1/textTranslated:
The restaurant is open from Monday to Friday: 6:30 am - 1:30 pm (closed on Saturday and Sunday) 
Quang noodles 55k/ portion mixed with shrimp, chicken, pork, and tea (artichoke) sold from morning to noon, many days the restaurant is sold out early, so go in the morning before noon, it's less crowded and there are still dishes left. 
Office lunch is sold from 11 am to 1:30 pm, priced at 45k/ portion including rice + soup + stir-fried dishes + savory dishes (free iced tea is served when sitting at the restaurant). The daily menu has 8 dishes and changes every day, you can add the owner on Zalo to order delivery, avoid waiting and avoid running out of your favorite dishes

reviews/0/text: Such a great Japanese restaurant. I don't tent to seek out foods from other countries when I am travelling, especially as this was my first time in Vietnam and had a lot of local options I wanted to explore. But this came recommended and it did not disappoint. Yakitori is always good in my mind, as are most foods cooked over charcoal. And this was no exception. But the standout course of the omakase was the chicken sashimi. A delight, a revelation. But everything was delicious, from the pickles, to the main show, right through to the wasabi sorbet at the end.
reviews/1/text: Portions are very small for the price. Avoid the chicken salad, the chicken had a jelly-like coating. When i asked about it, they said it was due to the powder but didn't offer to re-cook or deducte from the bill. The chicken in the salad was uneatable

title: Bò Bía cô Lý
address: 120E Đ. Lê Văn Duyệt, Đa Kao, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh 71007, Vietnam
reviews/0/text:
Mặc dù chỉ là xe bò bía nhỏ nằm ở góc đường Đinh Tiên Hoàng nhưng nơi đây lại trở thành điểm hẹn lý tưởng của thực thần là fan của món bò bía Sài Gòn. Bò bía Lý nức danh gần xa về độ thơm ngon, đầy đặn. Cuốn bò bía ú nu với phần bánh tráng mỏng dẻo ở bên ngoài, nhân bên trong gồm rau sống, củ sắn, lạp xưởng, trứng sợi…

Tất cả được gói chặt tay, còn độ ấm nóng tạo, khi ăn chấm cùng nước tương ngọt ngọt tạo nên sự hài hòa về hương vị. Quán bán vỉa hè, chỉ có vài con ghế bắc tạm nhưng không lúc nào ngơi khách. Nếu bạn chưa biết ăn gì ở Sài Gòn vào buổi xế thì chần chờ gì nữa mà không ghé ngay đến bò bía Lý.
reviews/0/textTranslated:
Although it is just a small spring roll cart located at the corner of Dinh Tien Hoang Street, this place has become an ideal meeting place for foodies who are fans of Saigon spring rolls. Ly spring rolls are famous far and wide for their deliciousness and fullness. The spring roll is plump with a thin, flexible rice paper layer on the outside, the filling inside includes raw vegetables, cassava, Chinese sausage, shredded eggs...

All are wrapped tightly, still warm, when eaten dipped in sweet soy sauce, creating a harmony of flavors. The shop is on the sidewalk, with only a few temporary chairs but is always crowded. If you don't know what to eat in Saigon in the afternoon, don't hesitate to visit Ly spring roll.
reviews/1/text: Ngồi tính nhẫm mới biết ăn ở đây 15 năm rồi. Cuốn to , đầy nhân… mình từng đến nhà cô lấy bò bía đặt sớm… sạch sẽ nhiệt tình vui vẻ. Giá xứng đáng chất lượng nha… cô thoải mái nước chấm , cho tự múc luôn.
reviews/1/textTranslated: I just realized I've been eating here for 15 years. The rolls are big and full of filling... I've been to her house to get spring rolls and ordered them early... clean, enthusiastic and cheerful. The price is worth the quality... she gives you plenty of dipping sauce and lets you scoop it yourself.
reviews/2/text:
Cuốn to đùng, ăn còn ấm hổi, nhân đầy đặn, rất chất lượng.

Nước chấm tự pha, có dầu tỏi và hành phi lấy tùy thích, cô vẫn vui vẻ nha.
Cô bán dễ thương, tiếc là chỉ bán đến 18h hoặc khi hết sớm.

Chỗ ngồi vỉa hè nên tùy duyên trời nắng mưa.
Có khăn giấy khi ăn.

Ăn bò bía đây xong qua gỏi khô bò ông Năm, (Nguyễn Văn Thủ) ăn gỏi khô bò vị SG xưa nữa là đúng bài.
reviews/2/textTranslated:
The rolls are huge, still warm, full of filling, very good quality.

The dipping sauce is homemade, with garlic oil and fried onions to choose from, she is still happy.
The seller is cute, unfortunately she only sells until 6pm or when sold out early.

The seats are on the sidewalk so it depends on the weather.

There are tissues when eating.

After eating spring rolls here, go to Mr. Nam's dried beef salad (Nguyen Van Thu), eat the old SG-style dried beef salad, it's the right thing to do.

Chỉ có tô bún bò là tạm ổn, bún riêu thì nước dùng nghe mùi bún bò, viên riêu toàn thịt heo xay; Tô bún mắm tệ nhất: chỉ có 1 con tôm, 1 miếng cá mỏng và 1 miếng râu mực nhỏ, còn lại toàn thịt heo mỡ nổi lềnh bềnh, nhìn thôi đã ớn rồi. Chỉ có dĩa rau sống là nhìn tươi ngon thôi. Cả nhà đã có một buổi tối đói meo
reviews/1/textTranslated: The restaurant is very big, convenient location, however the quality of the noodle dishes is not good. My family of 3 went, ordered: beef noodle soup, crab noodle soup, and fish noodle soup. Only the beef noodle soup was okay, the crab noodle soup had a broth that smelled of beef noodle soup, the crab balls were all ground pork; The worst bowl of fish noodle soup: there was only 1 shrimp, 1 thin piece of fish and 1 small piece of squid tentacle, the rest was all fatty pork floating, just looking at it made me sick. Only the plate of raw vegetables looked fresh and delicious. The whole family had a hungry evening.

Quán ko treo menu nhưng ko có để giá nên m cùn kk thích điều này
Nói chung tháy reciew khen nhưng ăn ko ngon. Mặc dù m rát thích mấy món như cháo/ mì hoành thánh/sủi cao
Nhưng quán ăn rất là bth nếu so với hà tôn quyền
reviews/0/textTranslated:
The restaurant is located right at the corner of the DBP roundabout, easy to find
The restaurant space is quite small and narrow, with 3 tables available so I mainly buy to go
The food is praised by reviews for the delicious fish porridge
But I tried the fish porridge and char siu noodles and found it normal, nothing special. In general, the elderly sell it, also gentle
The thing is, I didn't order iced tea but the owner brought it out and I told him I didn't order it before taking it away. I felt comfortable,
The restaurant doesn't hang a menu but doesn't have a price so I don't like this
In general, the reviews praised it but the food wasn't delicious. Although I really like dishes like porridge/wonton noodles/sushi
But the restaurant is very average compared to Ha Ton Quyen
reviews/1/reviewContext/Group size: Suitable for all group sizes, Not sure
reviews/1/text: Món hoành thánh ở đây rất ngon, vỏ mỏng dai vừa phải, nhân thịt thơm và nêm nếm vừa miệng. Nước dùng trong, ngọt thanh tự nhiên chứ không bị gắt. Ăn kèm rau và gia vị rất hợp, topping đầy đặn nên ăn xong khá no. Không gian quán sạch sẽ, phục vụ nhanh chóng và thân thiện. Rất đáng để quay lại thưởng thức.
reviews/1/textTranslated: The wontons here are delicious, the skin is thin and chewy, the meat filling is fragrant and well-seasoned. The broth is clear, naturally sweet and not harsh. It goes well with vegetables and spices, the toppings are plentiful so you are quite full after eating. The restaurant space is clean, the service is fast and friendly. It is worth coming back to enjoy.
reviews/2/text: Từ không gian cho đến hương vị món ăn, cách phục vụ đều mang đậm hoài niệm ngày xưa. Đặc biệt, quán có xá xị Chương Dương nhen.

reviews/1/text:
Vị trí: quán nằm ngay ngã 4 giữa Ng Văn Thủ và Cây Điệp, gần khu vực các toà nhà văn phòng, trường học nên buổi trưa quán có lượng khách kha khá.

Menu đa dạng sự lựa chọn của Mì quảng như thịt heo, sườn, gà, ếch,… với mức giá hơi nhỉnh một chút từ 50-70k/phần
Mình gọi tô mì quảng sườn + trứng cút là 50k, có 2 miếng sườn nhỏ, chắc tầm 5-6 trứng cút, nước dùng tạm tạm.
Bún chả cá đà nẵng thì ăn ổn, có chả cá, bí đỏ, chả bò mức giá 60k/tô.
Nhìn chung ăn được thôi nè.
reviews/1/textTranslated:
Location: the restaurant is located right at the intersection between Ng Van Thu and Cay Diep, near the office buildings and schools, so the restaurant has a fair number of customers at noon.
Space: relatively airy, clean, with an upstairs area.
The menu has a variety of choices for Quang noodles such as pork, ribs, chicken, frog, ... with a slightly higher price of 50-70k/portion
I ordered a bowl of Quang noodles with ribs + quail eggs for 50k, with 2 small pieces of ribs, probably about 5-6 quail eggs, the broth is okay.
The Danang fish noodle soup is okay, with fish cakes, pumpkin, beef cakes at 60k/bowl.
Overall, it's okay to eat.

reviews/0/text: 平日13時前に入店。Bún Đậu Mắm Tômの1人前とお茶をお願いしました。待つ事しばし。待っている間追加注文できるか確認。お願いしたものが出てきました。盛り付けきれいです。Đậu phụはアツアツです。チャーシューもうまい。Chả cáもうまい。基本全部美味しいです。Mắm Tômはすだちを入れグラニュー糖を少々入れて白い泡っぽいのがでるまでかき混ぜます。グラニュー糖を入れることで独特の臭みは薄らぎます。今日は唐辛子はなし。Đậu phụは追加注文。ついでにMắm Tômも追加注文。Đậu phụうまいです。次はChả cáを追加注文したいと思います。大変気の利く女性店員さんがいます。良いお店です。103kd。ごちそうさま😋。
reviews/0/textTranslated: I arrived just before 1pm on a weekday. I ordered a single portion of Bun Đậu Mắm Tôm and tea. I waited for a while. While I was waiting, I asked if I could order more. My order arrived. The presentation was beautiful. The Đậu phụ was piping hot. The char siu was delicious. The Chả cá was also delicious. Basically, everything is delicious. For the Mắm Tôm, I added sudachi citrus fruit and a little granulated sugar and stirred until a white foam-like consistency appeared. Adding the granulated sugar reduces the distinctive smell. No chili peppers today. I ordered another portion of Đậu phụ. I also ordered another portion of Mắm Tôm. The Đậu phụ was delicious. Next time I'd like to order another portion of Chả cá. The female staff were very attentive. This is a great restaurant. 103kd. Thank you for the meal 😋.
reviews/1/text:
Một buổi tối sau mưa, quán vắng.
Google maps chỉ vô hẻm, mình đi vào xong đi ra ngó mới thấy quán ngay mặt đường.

Đầu tiên thấy bún nhiều quá, bụng đang hơi ngang nên nghĩ là không ăn hết nhưng bằng một cách nào đó, thơm ngon hết miếng cuối cùng.

Tri ân đầu bếp bằng 1 review ghi nhận thực lòng.

One evening after the rain, the restaurant was empty.

Thanking the chef with a sincere review.

reviews/0/text: Quán Cơm Tấm Thịt Nướng này thật sự gây ấn tượng mạnh với tôi ngay từ lần đầu ghé thử. Không gian quán không quá lớn nhưng sạch sẽ, gọn gàng và tạo cảm giác thoải mái. Điều làm tôi thích nhất chính là hương vị thịt nướng. Miếng thịt được ướp vừa phải, thấm đều gia vị, khi nướng lên có mùi thơm đặc trưng, lớp ngoài hơi xém cạnh nhưng bên trong vẫn mềm, mọng và rất đậm đà. Cơm tấm được nấu tơi, không bị khô, kết hợp cùng mỡ hành nóng và tóp mỡ giòn rụm khiến mỗi miếng ăn đều rất tròn vị. Nước mắm pha theo kiểu truyền thống, không quá ngọt, có độ mặn và chua nhẹ hài hòa, làm nổi bật hương vị của các món ăn kèm. Dưa leo, cà chua và đồ chua luôn tươi và được chuẩn bị cẩn thận. Thời gian phục vụ khá nhanh, nhân viên nhiệt tình và thân thiện. Mức giá so với chất lượng thì hoàn toàn xứng đáng. Nếu bạn đang tìm một nơi để thưởng thức cơm tấm kiểu Việt Nam đúng chuẩn, đậm đà và đáng nhớ, tôi nghĩ quán này chắc chắn là một lựa chọn tuyệt vời. Tôi chắc chắn sẽ quay lại nhiều lần nữa cùng bạn bè và gia đình.
reviews/0/textTranslated: This Grilled Pork Broken Rice Restaurant really impressed me from the first time I visited. The space of the restaurant is not too big but it is clean, tidy and comfortable. What I like most is the taste of grilled meat. The meat is marinated just right, well-seasoned, and when grilled, it has a characteristic aroma, the outside is slightly charred but the inside is still soft, juicy and very flavorful. The broken rice is cooked loosely, not dry, combined with hot scallion oil and crispy pork rinds, making each bite very flavorful. The fish sauce is mixed in the traditional style, not too sweet, with a harmonious salty and sour taste, highlighting the flavors of the side dishes. Cucumbers, tomatoes and pickles are always fresh and carefully prepared. The service time is quite fast, the staff is enthusiastic and friendly. The price compared to the quality is completely worth it. If you are looking for a place to enjoy authentic, flavorful and memorable Vietnamese broken rice, I think this restaurant is definitely a great choice. I will definitely be back many more times with friends and family.

Co.opmart Cống Quỳnh is a really convenient spot for all sorts of food and household essentials.
They sell ready-to-eat meals, snacks and even food souvenirs, which is great if you want to bring something back home.
The selection is a bit limited compared to bigger supermarkets, but it’s still good enough for a quick grocery run or picking up some treats.
Bonus: They sell durian here. Lol

The staff and security here were very friendly and helpful.
I especially appreciated that they found me a box to carry my food instead of using plastic bags — little things like that make a big difference!

The store can get very crowded, especially during peak hours, but the checkout and service were surprisingly fast.

There’s also a convenient Grab drop-off and pick-up point right outside, which makes coming here really easy.

Overall, Co.opmart Cống Quỳnh is a solid choice for groceries, snacks, or souvenirs when you’re in the area. I’d definitely come back again!

reviews/0/text: Hello to Annam Gourmet Market employees. The person at the cashier in the deserts section of the store fooled me when I was asking weather the chocolate glazed doughnut they are selling was fresh — I was told it was freshly baked in the morning on the day of my visit, and my visit was ~ around 13:10 PM — after having a single bite of it it became obvious that this was not true, because the doughnut was stale (even judging by the photo this is visible). Upon further discussion with another employee from the cafeteria here I was afterwards provided the information that the doughnut was not fresh but previously frozen. So I got a refund. Wasted my time on getting here because the other day I was planning to come here to get this item specifically. Attaching photos for proof.
reviews/1/text:
Hôm nay mình ghé chi nhánh này lúc khoảng 4h thì có 1 ng bảo vệ chặn mình lại đòi khoá túi của mình. Điều đáng nói là gặp người nước ngoài thì im thin thít còn mình là người Việt Nam thì bị chặn lại đòi khoá túi.
Ủa mà, có hiểu cảm giác khi mỗi mình bạn bị chặn lại, bị khoá túi không? Tui đã ăn cướp gì của cửa hàng bạn mà bị xem thường vậy? Tui chỉ muốn đi vô kiếm món bánh mình thích và rời đi thôi mà cũng đáng bị xem thường vậy sao?
Mà kiểu chỉ mỗi mình mình bị thôi mới bực chứ.
Cửa hàng ko ngăn được trộm thì dẹp đi. Xem thường người Việt ngay trên nước Việt Nam.

Today, I dropped by this branch around 4 PM and a security guard stopped me, insisting that I lock up my bag.
The thing is, when foreigners come in, they say nothing — but when it’s me, a Vietnamese person, they stop me and demand to lock my bag.

Do you even understand how it feels to be the only one who gets stopped and told to lock their bag?
What, did I steal something from your store? Is that why I’m being treated like this?
All I wanted was to walk in, grab the snack I like, and leave — and even that earns me this kind of disrespect?

It’s even more upsetting because I was the only one treated that way.
If your store can’t handle theft properly, then maybe just shut it down.
Don’t look down on Vietnamese people in our own country.
reviews/1/textTranslated:
Today, I visited this branch at around 4 PM and a security guard stopped me and asked to lock my bag. The thing is, when meeting foreigners, they kept quiet, but I, a Vietnamese, was stopped and asked to lock my bag.
Oh, do you understand the feeling when you are the only one stopped and have your bag locked? What did I steal from your store to be looked down upon like that? I just wanted to go in and get my favorite cake and leave, but I deserve to be looked down upon like that?
It's annoying that only I am being treated like that.
Stores that can't stop thieves should just close them down. Look down on Vietnamese people right in Vietnam.

- Chả giò chiên sẵn nên hơi yểu, nhân cũng không đặc biệt, không nên gọi!

Sẽ đến thử bánh canh vào hôm sau
reviews/2/textTranslated:
The grilled pork noodle shop is hidden in the alley opposite the company so I stopped by for lunch. The space is simple and plain, with about 5-7 tables inside and outside, covered by a cool, pleasant silver screen. 

I ordered a bowl of spring roll noodle soup for 33K, plus a skewer of meat for 15K. The food here is very clean and has little seasoning, I found it easy on the stomach. 

- The grilled meat is not soft and fatty, but is lean meat so those who are not used to it will find it a bit dry. The seasoning is also moderate, not too sweet like the Western style in other restaurants. 

Pre-fried spring rolls are a bit weak, the filling is not special, should not order! 

Will come back to try the noodle soup tomorrow

address: 134 Cô Bắc, Phường Cô Giang, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/text:

reviews/0/textTranslated:
Delicious hamburger xs 😋

reviews/1/text:
Nếu ai mê bánh mì không thì đây chính là tiệm ngon nhất Sài Gòn theo cảm nhận của mình. Mình biết đến quán trong một lần ăn Ốc Đào: bánh mì ở đó đặc ruột, thơm đến mức phải hỏi nguồn, mới hay họ lấy mối từ tiệm này.

Quán nhỏ, chỉ bán mang về, vì ra bánh liên tục nên khách đến lấy đi rất nhanh.

Menu siêu gọn: Bánh mì thường (không đặc ruột): 3.000đ/ổ; Bánh mì đặc ruột: 6.000đ/ổ; Baguette dài: 9.000đ/ổ. Mình hay lấy ổ 6.000đ vì bột bánh cực thơm, ruột đặc dẻo, vỏ mỏng giòn. Ăn chấm bún bò, bò kho thì chuẩn, mà ăn không với phô mai + đường cũng tuyệt vời.

Phục vụ thường chưa tới 1 phút là xong giao dịch. Có lần mình ghé đúng lúc vừa hết mẻ 6k, các chú nói đợi 10 phút ra mẻ mới, chờ xíu để đổi lại bánh nóng giòn, quá xứng đáng.

Vote 5 sao và chắc chắn sẽ ghé mua mỗi khi thèm bánh mì “không” đúng chuẩn.
reviews/1/textTranslated:
If anyone loves bread, this is the best shop in Saigon in my opinion. I learned about the shop when I ate at Oc Dao: the bread there is so dense and fragrant that I had to ask for the source, only to find out that they source it from this shop. 

The shop is small, only sells take-out, because the bread is constantly being made so customers come and take it away very quickly. 

Super compact menu: Regular bread (not dense): 3,000 VND/loaf; Bread with dense filling: 6,000 VND/loaf; Long baguette: 9,000 VND/loaf. I often buy the 6,000 VND loaf because the bread dough is extremely fragrant, the inside is thick and chewy, the crust is thin and crispy. It is perfect to eat with bun bo or beef stew, but eating it alone with cheese and sugar is also wonderful. 

The service usually takes less than 1 minute to complete the transaction. Once I stopped by right when the 6k batch had just run out, the staff said they would wait 10 minutes for a new batch, wait a little longer to exchange for hot and crispy bread, it was so worth it. 

Vote 5 stars and will definitely come back to buy it whenever I crave "not" standard bread.
reviews/2/text: bánh mì rỗng ruột nhưng giới thiệu đặc ruột
reviews/2/textTranslated: Hollow bread but solid introduction

title: Chuối Nướng Cô Xuyến
address: 23A Trần Khắc Chân, Phường Tân Định, Việt Nam, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh 710880, Vietnam
reviews/0/text:
Trước đây, xe chuối nằm  chung mb với mấy xe đồ ăn vặt khác. Sau khi chủ nhà phía sau đập nhà để xây mới, không biết nay cô bán hàng đã chuyển  đi đâu .

Ở đây có bán chuối nếp nướng, xôi nếp nướng, chuối ép nướng và bánh chuối hấp. Tất cả dều được ăn chung với nước dừa có hành và có cả mỡ hành để riêng nếu ai muốn ăn thêm. Nước cốt dừa ngon béo, ngọt vừa phải, mùi mỡ hành thơm thơm. Các loại chuối và bánh chuối cô làm cũng ngon nữa, không thua gì mấy chỗ hay được lên báo. Mình hay ăn chuối ép nướng với nước dừa mỡ hành, sự kết hợp chuẩn không cần chỉnh.

Giá cả khá rẻ, đồng giá 15k cho 1 ly,mình haymua hộp thì nhiều hơn nên giá cao hơn
reviews/0/textTranslated:
Previously, the banana cart was located in the same area as other snack carts. After the owner of the house behind demolished the house to build a new one, I don't know where the seller has moved to. 

Here they sell grilled sticky rice bananas, grilled sticky rice, grilled pressed bananas and steamed banana cakes. All are eaten with coconut water with onions and scallion oil on the side if anyone wants to eat more. The coconut milk is delicious, fatty, moderately sweet, and has a fragrant scallion oil smell. The bananas and banana cakes she makes are also delicious, not inferior to the places that are often mentioned in the newspaper. I often eat grilled pressed bananas with coconut water and scallion oil, the combination is perfect. 

The price is quite cheap, 15k for a cup, I often buy a box because there are more so the price is higher

reviews/0/text:
Canh bún ngon. Rất thích. Ghé nhiều lần. Lần nào cũng ghé vào buổi trưa nắng nóng + quán ở vỉa hè thôi + mình sợ nóng + mà vẫn ghé => là mn biết mình thích cỡ nào r á 😁

1 tô to vầy nè, topping ngập mặt ứ hự v k á. Trời ơi cảm giác cắn quài k hết ốc là thế này chứ thế nào nữaaaa. Mn ghé tầm 11:30 - 12h là sẽ đông dữ nha. Cô bày có 3 bàn thôi huhu nên mn có thể đến sớm hơn hoặc trễ hơn khung giờ này xíu. Với lại cô bán vỉa hè thôi nên mn canh giờ + coi dự báo thời tiết r hẵng ghé nha, k thôi bị dính mưa là xu luôn

Chỉ có điều mình k thích lắm là tgian này cô k nhận thanh toán bằng cách chuyển khoản nữa, phải trả tiền mặt mn ạ. Còn lại thì k vấn đề gì, mình rất thích 🥳🥳
reviews/0/textTranslated:
The noodle soup is delicious. I really like it. I come here many times. I always come here on a hot sunny afternoon + the shop is on the sidewalk + I'm afraid of the heat + but I still come here => you know how much I like it 😁

A big bowl like this, the toppings are so full that it's so full. Oh my god, the feeling of not being able to finish eating snails is like this. If you come around 11:30 - 12:00, it will be very crowded. She only has 3 tables huhu so you can come a little earlier or later than this time. Also, she only sells on the sidewalk so you should watch the time + check the weather forecast before coming, otherwise if you get caught in the rain, you'll be fine

The only thing I don't like is that she doesn't accept payment by bank transfer anymore, you have to pay in cash. Otherwise, there's no problem, I really like it 🥳🥳

reviews/2/textTranslated:
The Bun Moc restaurant is hidden in a small alley on TKC street, I don't know how long it has been there, but I've known and enjoyed it for more than 10 years. Homemade meatballs are very delicious, chewy and of high quality, without any flour mixed in. The broth is rich. You can eat as much vegetables as you like. In addition, the restaurant also sells vermicelli, chicken and pork offal noodles. The main dish is still Bun Moc.
The owner is very enthusiastic and knows how to please customers.

title: Xôi heo quay cô Mai
address: 68 Trần Quang Khải, Phường Tân Định, Quận 1, Thành phố Hồ Chí Minh, Vietnam
reviews/0/text: Ladies are suuuuper sweet, I’ve been stalking this place missing sticky rice i and finally made my way cutting through the alleys; living up to loving her dish. Go show her some love, meal is A1 and some.
reviews/1/text:
Quầy cô Mai bán đủ món chứ không chỉ mình xôi  mình thấy có bánh mì, xôi, bánh ướt, bánh giò,bánh chưng,bánh dầy ... rất đa dạng. Đa số mua mang đi, khẩu phần món nào cũng khá ớn với giá phải chăng nhưng mặt bằng chung mình thấy chỉ ở mức ăn tạm được, mức khá.

Cô Mai nổi tiếng với xôi heo quay, xôi nem nướng ,, xôi chả cá và mình đều ghé vài ngày để mua đủ vị. Mỗi hộp xôi đồng giá 35k, cực nhiều topping.  Mình còn mua thêm bánh ướt nem nướng.
- Xôi dẻo nhưng hơi nhão và đóng cục bết lại, không rời hạt.
- Topping nền có pate, chà bông, chả lụa, trứng cút rồi sau đó mới cho thêm chả cá,heo quay, nem nướng tùy theo oder. mình thấy ngon nhất là nem nướng, cục to và dai dai, thơm ngon. Còn heo quay và chả cá thì hơi chán.
- Bánh ướt nem nướng giá 25k. chỉ có 4 cục nem nướng nhưng khá lớn. nước mắm pha nhạt nhạt, nên vị món này thấy không ngon cho lắm.

Chị em cô Mai bán hàng nhiệt tình và hào phòng, hay múc thêm xôi và tặng đồ cho khách. Và lần sau mình ghé thì chắc chỉ mua xôi thôi, mấy món còn lại không muốn nói thẳng và DỞ á, nên mình sẽ không đi sâu vô
reviews/1/textTranslated:
Ms. Mai's stall sells a variety of dishes, not just sticky rice. I saw bread, sticky rice, wet rice cakes, rice cakes, square rice cakes, round rice cakes... very diverse. Most of them are take-away, the portion of each dish is quite big with reasonable prices, but in general, I find it only acceptable, average. 

Ms. Mai is famous for sticky rice with roasted pork, grilled pork rolls, and grilled fish sticky rice, and I always stop by a few days to buy all the flavors. Each box of sticky rice costs 35k, with a lot of toppings. I also buy more grilled pork rolls. 
- Sticky rice but a bit mushy and clumpy, not separate grains. 
- The base toppings include pate, pork floss, pork roll, quail eggs, and then add grilled fish, roasted pork, grilled pork rolls depending on the order. I find grilled pork rolls the best, big and chewy, delicious. Roast pork and grilled fish rolls are a bit boring. 
- Grilled pork rolls cost 25k. There are only 4 grilled pork rolls but they are quite large. The fish sauce is too light, so the taste of this dish is not very good.

Ms. Mai's sisters are enthusiastic and generous, often scooping out more sticky rice and giving away gifts to customers. And next time I come, I will probably only buy sticky rice, the rest of the dishes are BAD, I don't want to say directly, so I won't go into detail.
reviews/2/text: Eo ôi xôi cô ngon cực rẻ nữa ! Chắc cô bán xuất ăn cho người lao động với sinh viên chứ trên con đường quận 1 mà hộp xôi to đầy ụ đủ vị có 25k ăn no tới cả chiều ạ ! Em ăn hết cả xôi còn tận nữa hộp topping các bác ạ 😙
reviews/2/textTranslated: Oh my gosh, your sticky rice is delicious and super cheap! You must sell meals to workers and students, because on a street in District 1, a big box of sticky rice full of all flavors for only 25k can keep you full all afternoon! I ate all the sticky rice and half a box of toppings, guys 😙
